body:
Other simulators support $get_initial_random_seed (guess this is non-standard, but all tools seem to have a version). Does not sound too hard to add support, unless one exists already in Verilator.

Thanks

```verilog
module tb();
    integer seed = 1;

    initial
    begin
        #5;
        seed  = $get_initial_random_seed();
        $display("seed=%0d", seed);
    end

endmodule
```

